---
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Waterm"
  description="Privacy Policy for Waterm, an SSH terminal app for iOS and macOS by Vivy Technologies Co., Limited."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
  ogType="article"
>
  <LegalPage title="Privacy Policy" lastUpdated="June 10, 2026">
    <section>
      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Vivy Technologies Co., Limited ("we", "our", or "us") operates Waterm, an SSH terminal
        application for iOS and macOS. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect
        your information.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>Server Configurations</h3>
      <p>
        Waterm stores your server configurations (host, port, username) locally and syncs them via
        iCloud to your other devices. This data is encrypted in transit and at rest by Apple's iCloud
        infrastructure.
      </p>
      <h3>Credentials</h3>
      <p>
        SSH passwords and private keys are stored in Apple Keychain. If iCloud sync is enabled,
        credentials sync via iCloud Keychain across your devices. We never receive these credentials,
        and they are protected by your device's security.
      </p>
      <h3>Analytics Data</h3>
      <p>
        We use Umami Analytics, a privacy-focused analytics service, to collect anonymous usage
        statistics on our website and in the app. The data is anonymous, processed on our own
        self-hosted analytics server, and never shared with third-party analytics companies or ad
        networks.
      </p>
      <p>
        We never collect the contents of your terminal sessions, the commands you type, your server
        addresses, usernames, file contents, or anything that identifies you. You can turn off app
        analytics at any time in Settings under "Help Improve Waterm".
      </p>
      <h3>Purchase Information</h3>
      <p>
        If you purchase Waterm Pro, your purchase is processed through the App Store. We receive
        confirmation of your purchase but do not have access to your payment details.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide and maintain the app functionality</li>
        <li>To sync server configurations across your devices via iCloud</li>
        <li>To verify Pro subscription status</li>
        <li>To improve our website and application</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p>
        Server configurations are synced via Apple iCloud, subject to Apple's security measures.
        Credentials are stored in Apple Keychain and may sync via iCloud Keychain when enabled. The
        only data our own servers receive is the anonymous usage statistics described above. We do
        not sell or share your personal information with third parties.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Delete all app data by removing Waterm from your devices</li>
        <li>Disable iCloud sync in Settings to keep data local only</li>
        <li>Remove stored credentials from Keychain at any time</li>
        <li>Turn off anonymous usage statistics in Settings ("Help Improve Waterm")</li>
        <li>Request information about data we may have collected</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact
        <a href="mailto:waterm@vivy.company"> waterm@vivy.company</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
